headline: EQT Expands Beyond Energy With US$6.6b Urbaser Deal And Valuation Gap
summary: EQT (NYSE:EQT) and Blackstone agreed to acquire Spanish waste management company Urbaser for $6.6b. The deal moves EQT beyond its core energy operations into global environmental infrastructure and waste services. The partners plan to focus on industrial and municipal waste, expanding Urbaser’s presence in these segments. EQT, trading at $58.7, is best known as a major US energy producer, so this Urbaser deal represents a clear shift toward environmental services. The stock has seen a 16.1%...
